#. Tag: title
#: ui.docbook:2
#, no-c-format
msgid "The User Interface"
msgstr "Uporabniški vmesnik"

#. Tag: title
#: ui.docbook:5
#, no-c-format
msgid "The &symboleditor; Main Window"
msgstr "&symboleditor; Glavno okno"

#. Tag: para
#: ui.docbook:6
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The main window consists of a tabbed widget containing the symbol editor and "
"a library view. There is a menu bar and several tool bars containing "
"standard actions, editing tools and rendering options. The status bar gives "
"prompts for using the various tools."
msgstr ""
"Glavno okno je sestavljeno iz pripomočka z zavihki, ki vsebuje urejevalnik "
"simbolov in pogled knjižnice. Obstaja menijska vrstica in več orodnih "
"vrstic, ki vsebujejo standardna dejanja, orodja za urejanje in možnosti "
"upodabljanja. Vrstica stanja daje pozive za uporabo različnih orodij."

#. Tag: title
#: ui.docbook:12
#, no-c-format
msgid "Editor Window"
msgstr "Okno urejevalnika"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: ui.docbook:15
#, no-c-format
msgid "Here is a screen shot of the &symboleditor; editor window"
msgstr "Tukaj je posnetek zaslona &symboleditor; okno urejevalnika"

#. Tag: para
#: ui.docbook:19
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Editor window allows editing of a symbol using the available tools. It "
"consists of a grid providing snap points and shows a preferred size guide "
"which allows symbols to be created to a consistent size. The size of the "
"grid, the number of elements and the preferred size guide are all "
"configurable."
msgstr ""
"Okno urejevalnika omogoča urejanje simbola z uporabo razpoložljivih orodij. "
"Sestavljen je iz mreže, ki zagotavlja zaskočne točke in prikazuje prednostni "
"vodnik po velikosti, ki omogoča ustvarjanje simbolov dosledne velikosti. "
"Velikost mreže, število elementov in želeni vodnik velikosti so nastavljivi."

#. Tag: para
#: ui.docbook:25
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The editor provides guidelines for positioning points relative to existing "
"points. The guides are positioned on the horizontal, vertical and diagonal "
"vectors from an existing point and also on a circular reference around the "
"center of the grid."
msgstr ""
"Urejevalnik nudi smernice za pozicioniranje točk glede na obstoječe točke. "
"Vodila so postavljena na vodoravne, navpične in diagonalne vektorje od "
"obstoječe točke in tudi na krožno referenco okoli središča mreže."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: ui.docbook:31
#, no-c-format
msgid "Here is a screen shot of the editor guides"
msgstr "Tukaj je posnetek zaslona vodil urejevalnika"

#. Tag: title
#: ui.docbook:40
#, no-c-format
msgid "Library Window"
msgstr "Okno knjižnice"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: ui.docbook:43
#, no-c-format
msgid "Here is a screen shot of the &symboleditor; library window"
msgstr "Tukaj je posnetek zaslona &symboleditor; okno knjižnice"

#. Tag: para
#: ui.docbook:47
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The library window shows representations of the symbols contained in the "
"library. The symbol currently being edited is shown highlighted. Selecting a "
"symbol will open it in the editor so that it can be modified."
msgstr ""
"Okno knjižnice prikazuje predstavitve simbolov v knjižnici. Simbol, ki se "
"trenutno ureja, je označen. Če izberete simbol, se ta odpre v urejevalniku, "
"da ga lahko spreminjate."

#. Tag: para
#: ui.docbook:52
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is possible to open several instances of the SymbolEditor application and "
"copy symbols from one library to another using drag and drop. Ensure that "
"both library windows are visible, then click and drag the required symbol "
"from one library window to the other. The symbol will then be appended to "
"the target library."
msgstr ""
"Možno je odpreti več pojavkov aplikacije SymbolEditor in kopirati simbole iz "
"ene knjižnice v drugo z uporabo povleci in spusti. Prepričajte se, da sta "
"obe okni knjižnice vidni, nato kliknite in povlecite zahtevani simbol iz "
"enega okna knjižnice v drugega. Simbol bo nato dodan v ciljno knjižnico."
